text: Ashkan Saranjam (Persian: اشکان سرانجام; born 5 December 1989), known professionally as Fadaei (Persian: فدائی), is an Iranian rapper, singer, and songwriter. He is member of Moltafet music group. Fadaei's songs often have political and anti-Islamic Republic of Iran themes. == Career == He started his work by releasing "Iran Iran" a year after the 2009 Iranian presidential election protests mentioning the killing of Neda Agha-Soltan and the 2009 Kahrizak Detention Center disaster. == Discography == === Albums === * Adl (2012) * Hagh (2022) * Eshgh (2024) == References == Category:Living people Category:1989 births
